            <section class="section">
                <div class="container">
                    <h1 class="title plant-care has-text-centered">Air Plant Blooming Care</h1>
                    <div class="columns is-mobile is-centered is-vcentered">
                        <div class="column is-3">
                            <img src="assets/air_plant.jpg" alt="">
                        </div>
                        <div class="column is-5">
                            <div class="content">
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Some flowers bloom for a day, while others can last much longer up to a week or
                                        so.</li>
                                    <li>Fertilizing is a good way to get your plant to bloom and produce pups.</li>
                                    <li>Be careful when watering, not to submerge the bloom.</li>
                                    <li>Once the bloom died, you can snip or remove to help encourage the next phase of
                                        growth.</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <hr class="mt-5 mb-5"
                        style="height:2px; border-width:0; color:gray; background-color:gray; width: 100%; margin: auto;">

                    <div class="container">
                        <div class="content">
                            <h4 class="subtitle is-4">Light</h4>
                            <p>Air plants prefer indirect sunlight and should be placed where they will receive adequate
                                light.</p>
                            <h4 class="subtitle is-4">Water</h4>
                            <p>Air plants need occasional misting 3-4 times a week or when they appear to be super dry.
                                Soak for at least 10-15 minutes twice a month.</p>
                            <h4 class="subtitle is-4">Soil</h4>
                            <p>Air plants get nutrients in the air through their leaves. It is important to place them
                                where they can enjoy a good air circulation.</p>
                            <h4 class="subtitle is-4">Root System</h4>
                            <p>Yes! Air plants has roots. It allows the air plant to grow even upside down.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
